><div class="sec suppmat" id="pmed-0030361-st001"><h4>Table S1</h4><!--caption a9--><strong>Impact of Voluntary Household Quarantine on Households of Different Sizes: </strong><p id="__p66">(21 KB PDF)</p><div class="sup-box half_rhythm" id="idm140373771038768"><a href="/pmc/articles/PMC1526768/bin/pmed.0030361.st001.pdf" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl">Click here for additional data file.</a><sup>(22K, pdf)</sup></div></div></div><div id="idm140373771037168" class="tsec sec headless whole_rhythm"><div class="sec"><div id="ack" class="sec sec-first"><p id="__p68" class="p p-first">JTW, SR, and GML benefited from discussions during meetings of the Working Group on Investigating Interventions in Case of an Influenza Pandemic, convened by the Scientific Committee on Advanced Data Analysis and Disease Modeling, Hong Kong Centre for Health Protection. The authors thank Shabbir Ahmed, Ron Billings, and Anton Kleywegt for sharing their computational equipment, Neil Ferguson and Ben Cowling for helpful discussion, and Irene Oi Ling Wong and Patsy Chau for help with data retreival. All views expressed here are those of the authors alone and do not necessarily represent those of third parties.</p><p class="fn-group"><div><p id="__p69" class="p p-first-last">\n<strong>Author contributions.</strong> JTW, SR, and GML designed the study and interpreted results. JTW and SR designed the model. JTW implemented the model. CF contributed to the model design, and provided some analytical results that were used for validation. SR drafted the paper. JTW, SR, CF, and GML edited the paper.</p></div><p class="fn sec" id="n101"><p id="__p70" class="p p-first-last">\n<strong>Funding:</strong> The authors thank the following for research funding: the Research Fund for the Control of Infectious Diseases of the Health, Welfare and Food Bureau of the Hong Kong SAR Government (JTW, SR, and GML); the Georgia Cancer Coalition (JTW); the University of Hong Kong SARS Research Fund (SR and GML); and 